finish development before taking action. In this system, where Black plays ...
g6 and ...d5, this is the best square for the light-squared bishop unless
Black plays the aggressive ...h6 and ...g5 moves, in which case the bishop is
better on d3.} b6 {Black has to finish his development and get the
light-squared bishop into play.} 10. O-O {It is a good idea to secure the king
before taking action.} Bb7 {Black finishes his development and is ready for
some action.} 11. a4 {This is an important move. White takes some space on the
queenside, and also stops Black from doing the same with b5. Furthermore,
a4-a5 could be a great idea next.} a6 {The best positional move that prevents
a5 and strengthens the b5-square.} 12. Qb3 {This is the most active square for
the queen and the rooks are now connected. It is also a provocative move,
which invites Black to make a small positional mistake and play c4.} e6 {Black
supports the d5-pawn and slowly improves his position.} 13. Bd6 {These bishop
moves to empty spaces are amongst the toughest ones to find in chess. The idea
behind this move is to force the exchange of the dark-squared bishops, after
which White would get a nice grip on the dark-squares and could play Ne5 later
on.} Bf8 {It is painful for Black to look at the White bishop without trying
to exchange it. It is hard to suggest anything else for Black here.} 14. Bxf8 {
White carries out his plan and takes the bishop.} Kxf8 15. Ne5 {And now,
according to the plan, White puts the knight on e5 to get a nice grip on all
dark squares in the center.} Nxe5 {Black has to take the knight to decrease
the pressure.} 16. dxe5 Ne4 {This is certainly not a good idea. Now after the
exchange on e4 White will get immediate pressure on the d-file and the great
outpost on the d6-square. Also, the Black light-squared bishop is much worse
than the White one.} 17. Nxe4 {White immediately opens the d-file.} dxe4 18.
Rfd1 {Now White takes control of the only open file on the board.} Qc7 19. Rd6
{White has a big advantage. All of his pieces are better than Black's, he has
the only open file under control, and clear play with Rad1 to increase the
pressure.} *

